[
  {
    "id": 16274407,
    "position": 1,
    "description": "<link rel=\"stylesheet\" href=\"https://instructure-uploads.s3.amazonaws.com/account_107060000000000001/attachments/95443758/canvas_global_app.css\"><link rel=\"stylesheet\" href=\"https://instructure-uploads.s3.amazonaws.com/account_107060000000000001/attachments/95447800/canvas_global_app%20%25281%2529.css\"><div class=\"byui itm112\">\n<h2>Overview&nbsp;</h2>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Task:&nbsp;</strong>Post a little bit about yourself in the Microsoft Teams Channel&nbsp;</li>\n<li><strong>Purpose:</strong> This task will allow you to familiarize yourself with Microsoft Teams and get to know your peers.</li>\n</ul>\n<hr>\n<h2>Icebreaker</h2>\n<p>Unlike many online courses, we will&nbsp;<strong>not&nbsp;</strong>have discussion boards. All our conversations and opportunities to teach one another will be within Microsoft Teams (MS Teams). Therefore, it only makes sense that we conduct our Icebreaker within MS Teams as well. As you get into industry, you will collaborate and work within asynchronous tools such as MS Teams.&nbsp;</p>\n<p>You should have already joined the section's MS Teams Group. If not, please review the following page:</p>\n<ul>\n<li><a class=\"inline_disabled\" title=\"W01 Prepare: Collaboration - Microsoft Teams\" href=\"https://byui.instructure.com/courses/404048/pages/w01-prepare-collaboration-microsoft-teams\" target=\"_blank\" data-api-endpoint=\"https://byui.instructure.com/api/v1/courses/404048/pages/w01-prepare-collaboration-microsoft-teams\" data-api-returntype=\"Page\">W01 Prepare: Collaboration-Microsoft Teams</a></li>\n</ul>\n<p>Now that you have joined the section's MS Teams Group, you need to introduce yourself. This is a valuable exercise not just to get to know your peers, but this is especially valuable for your instructor to get to know you better.&nbsp;</p>\n<h3>Instructions&nbsp;</h3>\n<ol>\n<li>In MS Teams, create a post in the <strong>#Icebreaker</strong> Channel (Make sure you are posting in the correct channel)&nbsp;</li>\n<li>Your post should be a quick paragraph that contains the following:\n<ol>\n<li>Your name</li>\n<li>Where you are from</li>\n<li>What your planned major is&nbsp;</li>\n<li>Other things you want your teacher and peers to know about you</li>\n<li>A picture of yourself</li>\n</ol>\n</li>\n<li>Take some time to see others' posts and come back to the #Icebreaker Channel as you work with others throughout the semester.&nbsp;</li>\n<li>You are welcome to post to others' posts and start a conversation, but you will only be required to make your own initial posting.&nbsp;</li>\n<li>When you are done, complete the one-question quiz below.&nbsp;</li>\n</ol>\n</div><script src=\"https://instructure-uploads.s3.amazonaws.com/account_107060000000000001/attachments/95443786/canvas_global_app.js\"></script><script src=\"https://instructure-uploads.s3.amazonaws.com/account_107060000000000001/attachments/95447814/canvas_global_app%20%25281%2529.js\"></script>",
